# ============================================
# Paper Reviewer CLI Configuration
# ============================================
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values
# See docs/CONFIGURATION.md for detailed setup instructions
# See docs/TROUBLESHOOTING.md for common issues

# ============================================
# Google AI (Gemini) API Configuration
# ============================================
# Required: API key for PDF analysis using Google Gemini AI
# 
# How to obtain:
# 1. Visit https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
# 2. Sign in with your Google account
# 3. Click "Create API Key"
# 4. Copy the generated API key
#
# Format: String starting with "AIza" (e.g., AIzaSyBxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx)
# Security: Keep this key secret! Never commit it to version control.
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_google_ai_api_key

# ============================================
# Notion Integration Token
# ============================================
# Required: Internal integration token for Notion API access
#
# How to obtain:
# 1. Visit https://www.notion.so/my-integrations
# 2. Click "New integration"
# 3. Fill in details:
#    - Name: Choose a name (e.g., "Paper Reviewer")
#    - Type: Select "Internal"
#    - Associated workspace: Select your workspace
# 4. Click "Submit"
# 5. Copy the "Internal Integration Token" from the integration page
#
# Format: String starting with "secret_" (e.g., secret_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx)
# Security: Treat this token like a password. It provides access to your Notion workspace.
NOTION_TOKEN=your_notion_internal_integration_token

# ============================================
# Notion Database ID
# ============================================
# Required: ID of the Notion database where papers will be created
#
# How to extract:
# 1. Open your Notion database in a web browser
# 2. Look at the URL:
#    https://www.notion.so/workspace/DatabaseName-<DATABASE_ID>?v=...
# 3. Copy the DATABASE_ID (32-character hex string)
#
# Format: 32-character hexadecimal string (with or without dashes)
# Examples:
#   - With dashes: a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890
#   - Without dashes: a1b2c3d4e5f67890abcdef1234567890
#
# Important: Make sure your Notion integration has access to this database!
#   - Open database → "..." menu → "Connections" → "Add connections"
#   - Select your integration and confirm
#
# See docs/CONFIGURATION.md for detailed database setup instructions
NOTION_DATABASE_ID=your_database_id
